Laugh Fest, a variety fundraising event, was a night of laughter with comedy, performances and a massive turnout from our faves Omotola Jalade-Ekeinde, Beverly Naya, Chigurl, Bryan Okwara, the Mbadiwe Twins, Mercy Eke and many others. Laugh Fest, put together by Osas Ighodaro, who lost her sister to malaria, is fighting to eradicate malaria from the nation through her Joyful Joy Foundation. Celebrities from across the entertainment industry graced the event in support of Osas’ mission to make malaria a thing of the past. Check out the photos below. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1372702" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.bellanaija.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/IMG_4096-Laugh-Fest-20-Dec-2019.jpg?resize=2736%2C4104&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="2736" height="4104" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The post Omotola Jalade-Ekeinde, Chigurl & Beverly Naya are Fighting Malaria at Osas Ighodaro & the Joyful Joy Foundation’s Laugh Fest appeared first on BellaNaija – Showcasing Africa to the world. Read today!. Source: Bella Naija The Joyful Joy Foundation annual comedy fundraiser ‘Laugh Fest’ is happening in Lagos Date: Thursday, December 19th, 2019 Time: 5pm Venue: Terrakulture Arena, Victoria Island, Lagos This event promises to be an exciting and supportive course of raising funds towards the eradication of malaria in Nigeria. Laughfest is a variety… December 17, 2019 In "Entertainment" After an eventful day at the Fair and Festival, The Entertainment Fair and Festival (TEFFEST) concluded successfully on Friday, November 29th fortifying its leading position as the continent’s most important Entertainment Business platform. The dynamic atmosphere in the Podium Hall was shaped by the lively discussion, exchanges of expertise and… December 3, 2019 In "Entertainment" The first edition of the â€˜Meditol Walk Against Malariaâ€™ organised by Evans Ltd, a member of the Ekulo Group of companies, manufacturers of Meditol Anti-Bacteria and Anti-Mosquito soap in collaboration with Emzor P